_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     The function performs to provide the item/test surface plot in
     two-dimensional style.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     surface.2D(a1, a2, d, correlation = 0, azimuthal_angle = 0, colatitude_angle = 15, filename = "NA", type = "jpeg")

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

      a1: the item discrimination parameters for the theta 1  

      a2: The item discrimination parameters for the theta 2 

       d: The item difficulty parameters 

correlation: The correlation between theta 1 and theta 2. If the
          correlation does not equal to zero, the a1 and a2 will be
          transformed to maintain the orthogonal assumption of the two
          dimensions of thetas 

azimuthal_angle: The azimuthal viewing angle 

colatitude_angle: The colatitude viewing angle 

filename: The filename in which the user saves the plot; if the
          filename is provided, the function will automatically save
          the plot for the users by the provided filename. 

    type: The format of files in which the user saves the plot

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     The function performs to return the item/test surface plot with
     theta 1 as x axis, theta 2 as y axis and the respones probability
     as the z axis.

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

